Hello, Is somebody here who thinks that SpaceX is rather a marketing company than engineering? (I am not speaking about Tesla). Just look. We are continuously fed with plans and plans and plans to the Mars, to Starship, to Moon, etc. and is nothing happening in real. Why don't you Elon already sit those astronauts into the Dragon? Why don't you put the civilians into your Spacecrafts - what you promised? You are just talking and talking.
Look, the Starship and the announcement again. That is a rough model, a hoax.
The worst is that, that everybody is celebrating this "marketing" like it was already happened.
When real human passangers to ISS? Next year? Come on, Space Shuttle did that in the last decades, nothing new. How many abort tests do you need to catch the past?
NO moon vehicle, landing vehicle. Moon maybe 10 years.
Starship 20 years. Rather 30.
If you believe this tricky marketing, and not focus on reality, than they do it in 40 years.
Anybody?

-Wuhan (武漢T, 武汉S, WǔhànP) is a sub-provincial city in China, capital and most populous city in Hubei Province.
Located at the confluence of the Blue River and the Han River, in the 1920s the city was the capital of the left-wing nationalist government of Wang Jingwei, in opposition to that of Chiang Kai-shek.
-the Blue River (so called in French, Italian and Spanish because it does not have a bed made up of clayey substances
-Beside the Yellow River, the Blue River is the most important river in the history, culture and economy of China, and is traditionally considered the border between northern and southern China. The fertile areas of the river delta generate about 20% of the gross domestic product of the People's Republic of China. It crosses a wide range of ecosystems and is the habitat of several protected animal species. For thousands of years man has used the river for water, irrigation, health care, transportation, industry, border and war.
-However, in recent years the river has suffered severe environmental damage, due to the exploitation of agriculture, industry and adjacent cities, and has suffered the loss of numerous lakes, tributaries and adjacent marshes. Many segments of the river are now protected, and the part of the river that flows through Yunnan (Protected Area of the Three Parallel Rivers) is part of the UNESCO cultural heritage.
One hypothesis is: they have provisionally reclaimed marshy areas by introducing the reclaimed marsh waters into the blue river, the marsh waters are rich in insects that have affinity with malaria, the diet of those regions is mainly fish, so they have eaten the insects of the marsh waters introduced into the blue river.

On 5 July 2012, the National Diet of Japan Fukushima Nuclear Accident Independent Investigation Commission (NAIIC) proved that the causes of the accident were foreseeable and that the plant operator, Tokyo Electric Power Company (TEPCO), had failed to meet basic safety requirements such as risk assessment, preparedness to contain the damage.
Later the Japanese government, after banning access within a radius of 20 km around the power plant, ordered the evacuation of five other towns outside the area.[107] In the town of Tomioka, the farmer Naoto Matsumura remained in an attempt to feed the pets that were abandoned in the area.
